 Editor's note: If you have trouble viewing the livestream, please click here.JOHANNESBURG - Cosatu s sixth Central Committee meeting has resumed in Pretoria on Monday.It's expected to last for four days.Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa is expected to address the gathering after the federation disallowed President Jacob Zuma from making speeches at its events. The theme is unity and cohesion to advance socialism.The implementation of Cosatu s congress resolutions and campaigns will be discussed. Members will also prepare for the events of its alliance partners.This includes the SACP's congress and the ANC's policy and consultative conferences.Tweets about #CosatuCC FROM:@XoliMngambi since:2017-05-29 until:2017-05-30) eNCA